      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SMIRKIN SERENE (3) has been tackling the best of the mares of late and enjoys a big class drop off the Group 1 Queen Elizabeth II Mile here a fortnight ago. Owns a strong strike rate at this circuit and distance. Finds the right race and the good draw should give her every chance. ISTHISJUSTFANTASY (11) draws wide but will enjoy coming back to her own sex having produced some decent efforts against the boys of late, beaten less than 4m here last week. NAMAKA (10) raced wide from a similar barrier but proved too strong at this circuit and distance last week. Deserved that following a string of placings and could go on with it. SKY BLU (5) has put together a series of close-up efforts since coming from this barrier for a win over this distance here. Respect along with MISSAUDACIOUS (6) who has placed in her last three outings here, all from wider draws than this.",
